This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper discusses adversarial attacks and defenses in deep learning, which are active areas of research in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a new taxonomy for adversarial robustness of neural networks, which is relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence and neural computing. The paper also discusses the trade-off between adversarial robustness and accuracy, which is a topic of interest in cryptography and security.
